## Symmetric plots 

::: {.callout-note title="Question"}

Build the symmetric plots (biplots)  for correspondence analysis of Mortalitity data

:::




::::: {.content-visible when-profile="solution"}  

::: {.content-visible when-profile='solution'} 

### From the shelf 




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
plot.CA(ca_79)
```
:::




:::


::: {.callout-tip title='Solution'} 

### {{< fa jedi >}}




::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
(
prep_rows |> 
    ggplot() +
    aes(x=`Dim 1`, 
        y=`Dim 2`, 
        label=name, 
        size=prop, 
        fill=log10(inertia),
        color=log10(inertia)) +
    geom_point(alpha=0.75) +
    scale_size_area() +
    coord_fixed() +
    scale_fill_viridis_c(aesthetics=c("fill", "color"),direction = 1) +
    geom_point(data = prep_cols,
      aes(x=`Dim 1`, 
        y=`Dim 2`, 
        label=name, 
        size=prop, 
        fill=log10(inertia),
        color=log10(inertia)
      ),
      shape="square",
      alpha=.5,      
    )
) |> plotly::ggplotly()
```

