::: {.callout-tip title='Solution'} 

It is convenient to use distinct color scales for  rows and columns. 





::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
(
prep_rows |> 
    ggplot() +
    scale_size_area() +
    coord_fixed() +
    aes(x=`Dim 1`, 
        y=`Dim 2`, 
        text=name, 
        size=prop, 
        fill=log10(inertia)) +
    geom_point(alpha=0.75) +
    scale_fill_viridis_c(option="D") +
    geom_point(data = prep_cols,
      aes(x=`Dim 1`, 
        y=`Dim 2`, 
        text=name, 
        size=prop, 
        color=log10(inertia)
      ),
      shape="square",
      alpha=.5,      
    ) +
    scale_color_viridis_c(option="F") +
    theme_minimal(
    )  
)  |> plotly::ggplotly()
```

